var title_f30_42_31395="Calculation valve area AS";
var content_f30_42_31395=[" <div id=\"graphicsToolbar\">",
"  <div id=\"graphicsCopy\">",
"   &copy;2013 UpToDate",
"   <sup>",
"    &reg;",
"   </sup>",
"  </div>",
"  <div id=\"graphicsLinks\">",
"   <a href=\"?imageKey=CARD%2F77899&amp;source=image_view&amp;view=print&amp;elapsedTimeMs=1\" onclick=\"\">",
"    <img alt=\"Print this page\" src=\"./../images/icn_print.myextg\" title=\"Print this page\"/>",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"icontxt textLink\" href=\"?imageKey=CARD%2F77899&amp;source=image_view&amp;view=print&amp;elapsedTimeMs=1\" onclick=\"\" title=\"Print this page\">",
"    Print",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"etacLink\" href=\"#\">",
"    <img alt=\"Email graphic(s)\" src=\"./../images/icn_email.myextg\" title=\"Email graphic(s)\"/>",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"icontxt textLink etacLink\" href=\"#\" title=\"Email graphic(s)\">",
"    Email",
"   </a>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 470px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Calculation of aortic valve area in aortic stenosis",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 278px; height: 462px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    The left ventricular outflow tract (LVOT) diameter (red line), measured just under the aortic valve, is obtained from the long axis parasternal view (panel A); the diameter is 1.5 cm and the area 1.8 cm2. Using the apical four chamber view, the Doppler sample volume in the LVOT is obtained from a position that approximates the locus from which the diameter of the LVOT had been measured (panel B). Another approach uses the continuous wave Doppler, sampling the jet across the stenotic aortic valve in the apical four chamber view (panel C); the peak velocity is 4.7 meter/s, yielding a peak gradient of 88 mmHg, a mean gradient of 45 mmHg, a flow velocity integral (VTI) of 100cm, and a valve area of 0.27 cm2. With the Doppler probe over the right parasternal window, the stenotic jet shows a peak velocity of 5.4 m/s, a peak gradient of 117 mmHg, a VTI of 129 cm and a valve area of 0.21 cm2.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"    </div>",
"   </div>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
"</div>"].join("\n");
